’Ł@14c22ee17d116c5feab1867136bb8c765e7434643ef71adddc211e9c8a713efbŚTitle: title: export-env
Path: Examples
Content:
Set an environment variable.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> export-env { $env.SPAM = 'eggs' }


```
Set an environment variable and examine its value.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> export-env { $env.SPAM = 'eggs' }; $env.SPAM
eggs

```
